description.en:
The learners analyse which changes related to teaching methodology and school management, compared to the traditional school, help to supports pupils' readiness for copying with the changing world.
The topics include :
-	characteristics of the changing learning paradigm and how they reveal in Estonian schools;
-	teaching in diverse learning environments;
-	integration between subjects at primary level;
-	project-based learning at primary level;
-	examples of school innovations in Estonia (Open School, Waldorf School , Gaia School, value education schools, entrepreneurial schools, outdoor education schools).
